version: 1.0.4
version_description: Add support for playing audio when using consumable items via xsound and UI/server persistence.

- Add bridge/audio/cl-xsound.lua and bridge/audio/sv-xsound.lua to integrate with the xsound resource and broadcast/play positional audio.
- Expose new audio fields in item creation/edit flows: audioLink, audioVolume, audioLooped, audioReplicated; update client UI (cl-creation) to collect these values and validate audio URLs.
- Client now plays configured audio when an item is used (cl-main) and skips playback when the player has hands-up emote.
- Add IsValidAudioUrl and audio extension whitelist in client utils; rename image-related helpers for clarity.
- Persist audio metadata on server create/edit (sv-creation) and broadcast play requests from server (sv-xsound).
- Add Config.SoundResource and update fxmanifest (version bump + add bridge to escrow_ignore).
- Minor tweaks: drunk config gains hasVehicleEffects flag and client drunk behavior checks it; add debugPrint logging for used items and remove raw json print.

This enables configurable audio-on-use for consumables while ensuring hosts/extensions are validated and audio can be replicated to nearby players when requested.